items.title: Bogaerts shakes off early HBP, goes 4-for-7
items.summary: Grimacing, Xander Bogaerts turned to the third-base dugout, spiked his helmet on the ground and kneeled in pain. A pitch from Matt Andriese had run inside and caught the first batter of the game squarely on the hand.
